Sir John Major said SNP leader Nicola Sturgeon poses a 'real and present danger' to the UK . 
  He mocked Ms Sturgeon over her demand to play a role in propping up a Labour government . 
  He said she is 'not even bothering' to stand as an MP herself . 
  Sir John claimed the SNP would use any power to foster division and further their dream of the break up of the Union . 
  But Ms Sturgeon branded his comments 'an affront to democracy'